Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.84,0:14:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,celebrated as politicians statesmanship you know only comes up when you discuss
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.40,0:14:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,like Winston Churchill or somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.10,0:14:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And Reagan very often comes up as statesmanship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.50,0:14:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when he said to Russia, take down this wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.64,0:14:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he was speaking as a statesman, not as a president.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.28,0:14:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He already was president,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.54,0:14:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so he didn't have to speak towards presidency.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He was speaking as a statesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.13,0:14:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Khrushchev, take down this wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.98,0:14:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was speaking as a statesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.90,0:14:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So I differentiate between politician and statesman.
